
  <sn><md>### Pediastrum {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://img.algaebase.org/images/AC1F05100321924A6EIYBF5B65AA/p5GBnti9toDS.jpg)
:::
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQhXd3mRm9xEEVAcY8eea0fNAO8jdSMwZqlpvFWdA515rEgpSrCPevwkLWQ&amp;s=10)
:::
:::

+++ Structure Image
![img](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Nh-emon/QDoc/main/SES%202nd%20Year/Diversities%20in%20Plant%20Kingdom%20and%20Plant%20Physiology/LAB/resources/Pediastrum%20Structure.jpeg)
+++

* **Family:** Hydrodictyaceae
* **Group:** Green algae (Chlorophyceae)
* **Color:** Bright green
* **Size:** 50–500 µm (colony)
* **Habitat:** Freshwater ponds, lakes, ditches
* **Identification:** Flat disc-shaped colony; outer cells have horn-like projections.
