![img](https://realmicrolife.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/Phacus-lismorensis-Playfaier-Skuja-Drezepolski-Pochmann.jpg)
+++

* **Family:** Phacaceae
* **Group:** Euglenoids (Euglenophyceae)
* **Color:** Green
* **Size:** 20–150 µm
* **Habitat:** Stagnant freshwater, polluted ponds
* **Identification:** Leaf-like flattened cell with pointed posterior end.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Oscillatoria {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://naturaevision.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/oscillatoria.jpg)
:::
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1405999310/photo/micrograph-of-spirogyra.jpg?s=612x612&amp;w=is&amp;k=20&amp;c=ipl8s8wM11JP0ERD1wGn8dbQvbJDM2g2b0aEQJcIT2E=)
:::
:::

+++ Structure
![img](https://biologylearner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Separation-discs-in-Oscillatoria-filaments.jpg)
+++

* **Family:** Oscillatoriaceae
* **Group:** Cyanobacteria
* **Color:** Blue-green
* **Size:** 5–60 µm wide
* **Habitat:** Ponds, lakes, wet soil
* **Identification:** Long unbranched filament; oscillating movement.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Microcystis {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://observation.org/media/photo/30058369.jpg)
:::
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b4/Microcystis_aeruginosa.jpeg)
:::
:::

* **Family:** Microcystaceae
* **Group:** Cyanobacteria
* **Color:** Blue-green
* **Size:** 2–7 µm per cell
* **Habitat:** Nutrient-rich ponds and lakes
* **Identification:** Numerous tiny spherical cells embedded in mucilage.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Spirogyra {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/spirogyra-sp-algae-under-microscopic-view-chlorophyta-spirogyra-sp-algae-under-microscopic-view-chlorophyta-251524192.jpg)
:::
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
