:::
:::

+++ Structure
![img](https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTbP0tiWOS-KltAPp3EXKkEQGVKWKGOmH6wGA&amp;s)
+++

* **Family:** Scytonemataceae
* **Group:** Cyanobacteria
* **Color:** Blue-green to brownish
* **Size:** 8–20 µm wide filament
* **Habitat:** Moist soil, rocks, tree bark
* **Identification:** False branching with thick sheath.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Volvox {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://miro.medium.com/1*hltzXCE0GMcwMUh54UoDQQ.png)
:::
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRF4LqvZRtmTgMO0aEYDwweQzza2ze77mr-H7r2vW8Lr06bqlUvstvZfI8&amp;s=10)
:::
:::

* **Family:** Volvocaceae
* **Group:** Green algae (Chlorophyceae)
* **Color:** Green
* **Size:** 200–1000 µm colony
* **Habitat:** Freshwater ponds and pools
* **Identification:** Hollow spherical colony containing daughter colonies.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Chlorella {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://media.sciencephoto.com/b3/02/02/67/b3020267-400px-wm.jpg)
:::
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![img](https://utex.org/cdn/shop/products/2168_20Chlorella_20sp_45bc1cb0-87fd-4116-b4d3-253ecacef343_600x.jpg?v=1571945520)
:::
:::

+++ structure
![img](https://www.shutterstock.com/image-vector/structure-chlorella-singlecelled-green-algae-600w-1696831267.jpg)
+++

* **Family:** Chlorellaceae
* **Group:** Green algae (Chlorophyceae)
* **Color:** Green
* **Size:** 2–10 µm
* **Habitat:** Freshwater, damp soil
* **Identification:** Tiny spherical unicellular algae.
</md></sn><sn><md>### One-Line Identification Key

```text
Pediastrum  → Flat star-like colony
Navicula    → Boat-shaped diatom
Cyclotella  → Round diatom
Phacus      → Leaf-like cell with tail
Oscillatoria→ Unbranched filament
Microcystis → Mucilaginous colony
Spirogyra   → Spiral chloroplast
Scytonema   → Branched filament
Volvox      → Hollow green sphere
Chlorella   → Tiny single green cell
```
</md></sn>